    "notes": "Australia's largest utility-scale battery. 4-stage build-out to 700 MW / 3,160 MWh at the former Eraring Power Station site on Lake Macquarie, NSW. Stage 1 (460 MW / 1,770 MWh, Wartsila GridSolv Quantum) operational Jan 2026. Stage 2 (240 MW / 1,030 MWh, grid-forming) approved Jul 2024. Stage 4 (360 MWh, Wartsila Quantum3) construction commenced Dec 2025. Origin Energy developer and operator. Enerven (SA Power Networks) EPC. Originally proposed with Tesla Megapack technology during early EIS phase — subsequently switched to Wartsila."
